        </p>
      </answer>
    </exercise>

    <exercise>
      <statement>
        <p>
          <m>f(x) = \sinh^{-1} (3x)</m>
        </p>
      </statement>
      <answer>
        <p>
          <m>\frac{3}{\sqrt{9x^2+1}}</m>
        </p>
      </answer>
    </exercise>

    <exercise>
      <statement>
        <p>
          <m>f(x) = \cosh^{-1} (2x^2)</m>
        </p>
      </statement>
      <answer>
        <p>
          <m>\frac{4x}{\sqrt{4x^4-1}}</m>
        </p>
      </answer>
    </exercise>

    <exercise>
      <statement>
        <p>
          <m>f(x) = \tanh^{-1} (x+5)</m>
        </p>
      </statement>
      <answer>
        <p>
          <m>\frac{1}{1-(x+5)^2}</m>
        </p>
      </answer>
    </exercise>

    <exercise>
      <statement>
        <p>
          <m>f(x) = \tanh^{-1} (\cos x)</m>
        </p>
      </statement>
      <answer>
        <p>
          <m>-\csc x</m>
        </p>
      </answer>
    </exercise>

    <exercise>
      <statement>
        <p>
          <m>f(x) = \cosh^{-1} (\sec x)</m>
        </p>
      </statement>
      <answer>
        <p>
          <m>\sec x</m>
        </p>
      </answer>
    </exercise>

    <p>
      In the following exercises,
      find the equation of the line tangent to the function at the given <m>x</m>-value.
    </p>

    <exercise>
      <statement>
        <p>
          <m>f(x) = \sinh x</m> at <m>x=0</m>
        </p>
      </statement>
      <answer>
        <p>
          <m>y=x</m>
        </p>
      </answer>
    </exercise>

    <exercise>
